<paragraph blockId="40.[264,1323,1551,1817]" pageId="40" pageNumber="41">
Based on an examination of 
<typeStatus box="[603,665,1551,1577]" pageId="40" pageNumber="41">types</typeStatus>
(
<collectionCode LSID="urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:34871" box="[681,772,1551,1577]" httpUri="http://biocol.org/urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:34871" name="Smithsonian Institution, National Museum of Natural History" pageId="40" pageNumber="41">USNM</collectionCode>
), it is obvious that Smith named the two sexes of this species as different species: ‘ 
<taxonomicName box="[708,771,1591,1616]" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Polia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="40" pageNumber="41" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[708,771,1591,1616]" italics="true" pageId="40" pageNumber="41">Polia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
’ 
<taxonomicName box="[792,891,1591,1616]" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Hexorthodes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="40" pageNumber="41" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="montara">
<emphasis box="[792,891,1591,1616]" italics="true" pageId="40" pageNumber="41">montara</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is the male and ‘ 
<taxonomicName box="[1110,1173,1591,1616]" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Polia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="40" pageNumber="41" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1110,1173,1591,1616]" italics="true" pageId="40" pageNumber="41">Polia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
’ 
<taxonomicName box="[1194,1275,1591,1616]" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Hexorthodes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="40" pageNumber="41" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="nipana">
<emphasis box="[1194,1275,1591,1616]" italics="true" pageId="40" pageNumber="41">nipana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
the female. The name 
<taxonomicName box="[482,563,1631,1656]" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Hexorthodes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="40" pageNumber="41" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="nipana">
<emphasis box="[482,563,1631,1656]" italics="true" pageId="40" pageNumber="41">nipana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
appears first, and I treat 
<taxonomicName box="[856,955,1631,1656]" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Hexorthodes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="40" pageNumber="41" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="montara">
<emphasis box="[856,955,1631,1656]" italics="true" pageId="40" pageNumber="41">montara</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
as a synonym.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="40.[264,1323,1551,1817]" pageId="40" pageNumber="41">
The fact that 
<taxonomicName box="[473,592,1671,1696]" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Hexorthodes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="40" pageNumber="41" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="nipana">
<emphasis box="[473,592,1671,1696]" italics="true" pageId="40" pageNumber="41">H. nipana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was misplaced in 
<taxonomicName box="[818,881,1671,1696]" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Polia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="40" pageNumber="41" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[818,881,1671,1696]" italics="true" pageId="40" pageNumber="41">Polia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was pointed out by McCabe (
<number box="[1246,1310,1671,1697]" pageId="40" pageNumber="41" value="1980.0">1980</number>
). Based on the structure of the male genitalia (
<figureCitation box="[876,973,1711,1737]" captionStart="FIGURES 40 – 63" captionStartId="45.[264,362,1527,1551]" captionTargetBox="[292,1293,316,1500]" captionTargetId="figure@45.[292,1294,316,1504]" captionTargetPageId="45" captionText="FIGURES 40 – 63. Male genitalia of the new described species and related species: 40, Protoperigea calientensis (a, valve; b, everted vesica). 41, Aseptis fanatica (a, valve; b, everted vesica). 42, Aseptis ethnica. 43, Aseptis ferruginea. 44, Aseptis torreyana (a, valve; b, everted vesica). 45, Aseptis serrula. 46, Apamea robertsoni (a, valve; b, everted vesica). 47, Apamea digitula (a, valve; b, everted vesica). 48, Apamea sordens. 49, Photedes sofiae. 50, Mammifrontia sarae (a, valve; b, everted vesica). 51, Mammifrontia rileyi (a, valve; b, everted vesica). 52, Benjaminola colorada (a, valve; b, everted vesica). 53, Perigonica tertia. 54, Perigonica fulminans. 55, Perigonica angulata. 56, Anarta fusculenta (a, valves; b, everted vesica). 57, Anarta crotchi (a, valves; b, everted vesica). 58, Anarta oaklandiae. 59, Lasionycta sala (a, valves; b, everted vesica). 60, Trichocerapoda harbisoni (a, valves; b, everted vesica). 61, Trichocerapoda comstocki. 62, Trichocerapoda oceanis (a, valves; b, everted vesica). 63. Hexorthodes nipana." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/273512/files/figure.png" pageId="40" pageNumber="41">
Fig. 
<number box="[941,973,1711,1737]" pageId="40" pageNumber="41" value="63.0">63</number>
</figureCitation>
), 
<taxonomicName box="[1006,1134,1711,1736]" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Hexorthodes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="40" pageNumber="41" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="nipana">
<emphasis box="[1006,1134,1711,1736]" italics="true" pageId="40" pageNumber="41">H. nipana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
fits well into 
<taxonomicName box="[264,414,1751,1776]" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Hexorthodes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="40" pageNumber="41" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[264,414,1751,1776]" italics="true" pageId="40" pageNumber="41">Hexorthodes</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, for which McDunnough (
<number box="[735,796,1751,1777]" pageId="40" pageNumber="41" value="1943.0">1943</number>
) designated 
<taxonomicName authority="Smith, 1900" authorityName="Smith" authorityYear="1900" box="[948,1243,1751,1777]" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Hexorthodes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="40" pageNumber="41" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="serrata">
<emphasis box="[948,1071,1751,1776]" italics="true" pageId="40" pageNumber="41">H. serrata</emphasis>
(Smith, 
<number box="[1175,1235,1751,1777]" pageId="40" pageNumber="41" value="1900.0">1900</number>
)
</taxonomicName>
as the 
<typeStatus box="[264,314,1791,1817]" pageId="40" pageNumber="41">type</typeStatus>
species. This species has very similar genitalia to 
<taxonomicName box="[905,1022,1791,1816]" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Hexorthodes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="40" pageNumber="41" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="nipana">
<emphasis box="[905,1022,1791,1816]" italics="true" pageId="40" pageNumber="41">H. nipana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
